Took my little brother, @shane_puccio ,to Emerald Lake yesterday and decided to play around a little and did  some reverse climbing. 
.
Started at the end of “The Kind Traverse” and finished up “The Kind”.
Thought it felt like V11ish. To me, felt harder than The Kind Traverse. 
Anyone know if this has been done before??? 
Fun movement and a better finish!!! 👍😃
.
@scarpana @organicclimbing @frictionlabs @beam @kayaclimbing

.

.
@scarpana @evn_cbd

node.text:
Some BAD uncut footage of me sending “The Shining” V13/8B in RMNP a few years ago. I didn’t say I was going to try again so that’s why it starts one move or so into the climb, haha. I usually don’t like to say when I’m going to pull on and give a send burn, because I don’t like the pressure or to think about the camera being there. I just want to be in “The Zone” and present. ☺️✌️ was psyched I sent this boulder in 1 short session. .
.
I’ll keep posting some uncut and probably unedited footage over the next weeks. Motivation to stay fit and strong so when everything goes back to normal we can go send our projects!!! A blast from the past!!! 🤪 
@scarpana @organicclimbing @frictionlabs

Chalking up those sweaty damp hands before sending this crimpy little climb, “Dragons Tail” V10 ✅
.
Fell on the flash go on the last move, hands were slipping off. 

It was definitely a VERY humid and wet rainy day in the basin. Made every climb either not possible or a lot harder if it was “climbable”. 😆
But hey, we still got outside and enjoyed the day!!! 😅✅❤️
.

.

node.text:
2018 I got the opportunity to star in a fun commercial in Japan. This was also what @robinoleary and I like to say was our “2nd” date! 😂  This was truly an amazing experience I will never forget! 🙏😄
.
This was both of our first time to Japan and we fell in love with it instantly!!! 
Once the world is safe for traveling again we definitely will plan a trip back there to see more amazing places and climb outside!!! 😄❤️
.
@scarpana @organicclimbing @frictionlabs @beam

node.text:
Another amazing shoe by @scarpana , the Drago LV. 
I love the simplicity in the color, but yet still looks sharp and sleek! 
This shoes is great for bouldering and steeper sport climbing.
.
This coming Monday I will be doing a GIVEAWAY for a pair of @scarpana shoes!!! 
Keep an eye out on my IG this Monday for how to enter the GIVEAWAY to win any pair of @scarpana climbing or hiking shoes you want! 😄
.
Hope you all are enjoying the summer so far!!! 🌸⛰☀️
.
@scarpana @organicclimbing @frictionlabs

node.text:
One of my happy places! 
Being outside in the forest with chalk all over me, falling in the dirt, scrapes on my legs, crap in my hair, cuticles a mess, playing on some rocks with a big smile on my face!!! 😄🥰
.
Everyone’s happy place looks different, just make sure you go out and find yours!!! 💪🏻❤️
.
@scarpana @organicclimbing @frictionlabs
